================================================================
Third-party components
================================================================

- pmdmini (GPL-2.0-or-later)
  PMD sound engine. Authors of bundled sources actually used in this build:
    M.Kajihara  - PMD original author (PC-98)
    C60         - PMDWin Windows port (pmdwincore, pmdwin, opnaw, p86drv,
                  ppsdrv, table, util, sjis2utf, ppz8l Win port)
    UKKY        - PPZ8 PCM driver original author (ppz8l)
    BouKiCHi    - pmdmini library wrapper (pmdmini.cpp)
  https://github.com/mistydemeo/pmdmini
  Upgraded to GPL-3.0 under the "or-later" clause.

- ymfm (BSD-3-Clause)
  Copyright (C) 2021-2022, Aaron Giles
  https://github.com/aaronsgiles/ymfm
  Used for YM2608 (OPNA) FM and SSG synthesis. Bundled in
  pmdmini/src/ymfm/. Full license available in that directory.

- Media Engine library by m-c/d (mcidclan)
  Copyright (C) m-c/d
  https://github.com/mcidclan

  This project bundles an earlier version of m-c/d's Media Engine
  library work (the predecessor to psp-media-engine-custom-core / MECC),
  used in seplugin mode with a kcall.prx kernel bridge. The library
  files are located in the tiny-me/ subdirectory of this repository.

  See the upstream author's GitHub for related projects including
  the current version (MECC):
  - https://github.com/mcidclan/psp-media-engine-custom-core
  - https://github.com/mcidclan/psp-media-engine-reload

================================================================
NOT included - user must provide
================================================================

- YM2608 ADPCM Rhythm ROM (Yamaha Corporation)
  The Yamaha YM2608 ADPCM rhythm ROM is copyrighted by Yamaha and is
  NOT redistributed with this project. Users who wish to enable rhythm
  playback must obtain the ROM from their own hardware or legitimate
  sources, and place the file at:

      ms0:/PSP/GAME/PMDVIS/ym2608_adpcm_rom.bin
      (or ef0:/... on PSP Go)

  PMDVIS will operate without this file, but rhythm channels will be
  silent.
